label: City · Texas
name: Dallas
notes: Major metropolitan area in Texas and the site of the JFK assassination on November 22, 1963.

label: City · Louisiana
name: New Orleans
notes: Birthplace of Lee Harvey Oswald and a significant location for his activities in the summer of 1963.

label: City · Texas
name: Irving
notes: A suburb of Dallas where the Paine residence was located and where Lee Harvey Oswald spent the night before the assassination.

label: Public Square · Dallas
name: Dealey Plaza
notes: A city park in the West End district of downtown Dallas where President John F. Kennedy was assassinated.

label: Building · Dallas
name: Texas School Book Depository
notes: The workplace of Lee Harvey Oswald and the site from which the Warren Commission concluded he fired the shots that killed President Kennedy.

label: Private Residence · Dallas
name: Walker Residence (Turtle Creek)
notes: The home of General Edwin Walker at 4011 Turtle Creek Blvd, where an assassination attempt occurred on April 10, 1963.

label: Business · Dallas
name: Texas Butcher's Supply
notes: A business in Dallas where Ralph Leon Yates was employed and from where he purportedly picked up a hitchhiker matching Oswald's description.

label: Private Residence · Irving
name: Ruth Paine Residence (Irving)
notes: The home of Ruth and Michael Paine where Marina Oswald lived in late 1963 and where Lee Harvey Oswald kept his rifle.
